content.description: Immediately to the right of "fratboys with razorblades" is this bolted slab. It is a bit sharp, and is maybe a grade harder than its neighbor due to a delicate start.  Not phenomenal, but a good warm-up, and worth doing.  Not in the book.

Start under the left side of the bushy ledge, clip 3 bolts, and take the right line to the roof.  Find a couple good underclings and reach way up.  The crux tests your pocket power, and the rest is great 11- pockets through another bulge.
content.location: Find a bushy ledge 10' up.  The route starts under the left side of the ledge, then goes right after the third bolt.

content.description: Cool moves on a variety of holds snake up the techy vert section at the bottom.  A couple powerful pulls on pockets surmount the roof and deposit you at a rest.  One more in-obvious test guards the anchor.
content.location: Right of Lizard in a Bottle and left of Meat Head.  Goes up dark black vert wall through the roof.

content.description: Negotiate delicate face climbing using a seam for the first half.  Find the good pockets to surmount the bulge and keep moving before you get too pumped.  Easy finish.
content.location: Between Dust, Wind and Sorority Girl.

content.description:
Easy/slopey slab moves up a grey ramp, then fire up the short, overhanging wall on jugs and pockets to a thank-god anchor.

Gym rats and bouldering thugs will find this "11a" a gimmie. Probably a 10d.
content.location: The very first (left) line on the Frat Boys wall. Located in the middle of the massive limestone shiv that separates FB wall and Antarctica wall to the left.

content.description: Cruise up the lower slabby section to a rest below the roof.  Find good holds using the crack feature to climb out the largest part of this overhang.  Looks tougher than it turns out to be.  Climb good pockets to the top.
content.location: Between Meat Head and Theta Dorka.  Begins the same as Theta Dorka Tool Shed and steps left.

content.description: Follow thin, techy crack on a slab to better holds, finally moving right and surmounting a bulge.
content.location: Right of Frat Boys With Razor Blades, look for a thin flaring crack just left of where the half-height horizontal break/roof system begins.

content.description: Climb a thin slab to progressively better (and sharper) holds.  Feels airy near the top.  Huey's book is right, if you slice yourself open, you're off route!
content.location: First route right of big roof close to the ground, or about 60 feet right of the Big Man On Campus flake.

content.description: Climb a crack that is trickier than it looks to reach the pedastal.  Have lunch.  Figure out how to surmount the overhang and cruise to the top.  Another fine CK outing that got no stars (cats, hookers, flags, etc.) in the book.  I thought it was great.

A cool route that doesn't seems to get done very often.  Begins by 'cruising' up the slabby arete as Huey says to an actual top out, that leaves you standing in a cleft.  Reach up to find pockets on the lip and do a campus move to reach the next set of pockets.  At this point you can throw a heel or toe on to help attain the rest of the route.  A cool feature that really does work, even though it would seem easier to just go to the left and skip the fun part, its not!!  So just do it.
content.location: On the right arete of partially detached pillar at the left end of the Frat Boys Sector.
